      @multipart['body'].should eql "July 05, 2012\n\nWe've seen the future and it's looking mighty bright. With a bit of ingenuity and whole lot of ambition, projects this week explore the depths of the ocean, soar beyond the atmosphere, and take a plunge into the bold new world of self-publishing.\xC2\xA0\n\nOpenROV - The Open Source Underwater Robot (http://www.kickstarter.com/projects/openrov/openrov-the-open-source-underwater-robot?ref=NewsJul0512&amp;utm_campaign=Jul05&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_source=newsletter)\n by OpenROV\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nOpen Hardware (http://www.kickstarter.com/discover/categories/open%20hardware?ref=NewsJul0512&amp;utm_campaign=Jul05&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_source=newsletter)\n\nSan Francisco, CA (http://www.kickstarter.com/discover/cities/san-francisco-ca?ref=NewsJul0512&amp;utm_campaign=Jul05&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_source=newsletter)\n\nUnder the sea\n-------------\n\nOpenROV is a low-cost, open source robot designed to make underwater exploration possible for everyone. About the size of a shoebox, the compact robot can house a camera and explore almost any watery space, from your bathtub to the ocean. Whether you're a maker, hobbyist, or scientist, the OpenROV is sure to unlock your inner Jules Verne.\n\nExplore this project (http://www.kickstarter.com/projects/openrov/openrov-the-open-source-underwater-robot?ref=NewsJul0512&amp;utm_campaign=Jul05&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_source=newsletter)\n\n\n\n\nTomorrow Magazine (http://www.kickstarter.com/projects/tomorrowmag/tomorrow-magazine?ref=NewsJul0512&amp;utm_campaign=Jul05&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_source=newsletter)\n by Tomorrow Magazine\n-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nJournalism (http://www.kickstarter.com/discover/categories/journalism?ref=NewsJul0512&amp;utm_campaign=Jul05&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_source=newsletter)\n\nLos Angeles, CA (http://www.kickstarter.com/discover/cities/los-angeles-ca?ref=NewsJul0512&amp;utm_campaign=Jul05&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_source=newsletter)\n\nNew new media\n-------------\n\nWhat happens in the year 2012 when a newly-unemployed editorial team bands together for one last project? Tomorrow Magazine, that's what! Tomorrow will be the magazine these writers and designers always dreamed of making, featuring stories about opportunity, breaking from the status quo, and what comes next. Sounds appropriate!\n\nExplore this project (http://www.kickstarter.com/projects/tomorrowmag/tomorrow-magazine?ref=NewsJul0512&amp;utm_campaign=Jul05&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_source=newsletter)\n\n\n\n\nFinal Frontier Design's 3G Space Suit (http://www.kickstarter.com/projects/872281861/final-frontier-designs-3g-space-suit?ref=NewsJul0512&amp;utm_campaign=Jul05&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_source=newsletter)\n by Ted Southern\n---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nTechnology (http://www.kickstarter.com/discover/categories/technology?ref=NewsJul0512&amp;utm_campaign=Jul05&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_source=newsletter)\n\nBrooklyn, NY (http://www.kickstarter.com/discover/cities/brooklyn-ny?ref=NewsJul0512&amp;utm_campaign=Jul05&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_source=newsletter)\n\nOne small step\n--------------\n\nWith the fledgling commercial space industry making major strides, a fundamental problem for space travel remains in need of a better solution: the space suit. Artist Ted Southern has teamed up with veteran space suit engineer Nikolay Moiseev to develop an inexpensive, lightweight suit capable of providing astronauts with unprecedented mobility.\xC2\xA0Bulky space suits of yore are about to take a giant leap forward.\xC2\xA0\n\nExplore this project (http://www.kickstarter.com/projects/872281861/final-frontier-designs-3g-space-suit?ref=NewsJul0512&amp;utm_campaign=Jul05&amp;utm_medium=email&amp;utm_source=newsletter)\n\n\n\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\xE2\x80\x94\n\nCopyright 2010 Kickstarter Inc.\nKickstarter Inc. - 155 Rivington Street, New York, NY 10002.\n\n\n"
